relevant_findings.general: Morbidly obese, lying in bed on right decubitus, alert and oriented x3.
relevant_findings.eyes: Pupils equal, round, reactive to light; extraocular movements intact; conjunctiva clear and anicteric.
relevant_findings.cardiovascular: Regular rate and rhythm, normal S1 and S2, no murmurs, rubs, or gallops.
relevant_findings.pulmonary: Clear to auscultation, no rales, rhonchi, or wheezing.
relevant_findings.gastrointestinal: Normal bowel sounds, marked obesity, midepigastric tenderness, no rebound tenderness, difficult to assess for hepatosplenomegaly.
relevant_findings.extremities: Warm, no cyanosis, clubbing, or edema.
relevant_findings.neurological: Alert, oriented x3, answers questions appropriately, follows commands, non-focal.
